Package com.google.mu.util.stream

Class Case<T,​A,​R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.mu.util.stream.Case<T,​A,​R>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.stream.Collector<T,​A,​R>
    public abstract class Case<T,​A,​R>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.stream.Collector<T,​A,​R>
    Utility class to perform n-ary functional pattern matching on a list or a stream of input elements.

    A Case object can be used as a stand-alone Collector for a stream. For example: 

    
 import static com.google.mu.util.stream.MoreCollectors.exactly;

 stream.collect(onlyElements((a, b, c) -> ...));
    Or as one of several possible cases passed to the static findFrom() method. For example: 
    
 import static com.google.mu.util.stream.MoreCollectors.*;

 Optional<Path> path = Case.findFrom(
     pathComponents,
     onlyElements((parent, child) -> ...),
     onlyElements(fileName -> ...),
     firstElements(root -> ...));
    Since:
    5.3

    • Method Detail

      • findFrom

        @SafeVarargs
public static <T,​R> java.util.Optional<R> findFrom​(java.util.List<T> list,
                                                         Case<? super T,​?,​? extends R>... cases)
        Expands the input elements in list and transforms them using the first from cases that matches. If no case matches the input elements, Optional.empty() is returned.

        For example, to switch among multiple possible cases: 

        
 import static com.google.mu.util.stream.MoreCollectors.*;

 Optional<R> result =
     Case.findFrom(
         list,
         exactly((a, b) -> ...),
         firstElements((a, b, c) -> ...));
